metadata.name: UPLOAD.EXE #89
metadata.description:
No death in the metaverse 
100 billion mortal coils before us, reduced to silly memes 

Here then, a chance to right every wrong 
Or curse ourselves, forgetting we once counted days so keenly 

C:\SOULS>UPLOAD.EXE -commit -purge 
Irreversible operation. Are you sure? [Y/N] Y_ 

.....LFG 

---------------------------------------------------- 


Additional params 

&fullsize=true : 4096x4096 output 
&debug=true : Display generative figure outlines  
&notilt=true : Remove tilt-shift filter 


References 

How to draw a basic Human Figure Using Circles Only - Photoshop - Easy Anatomy Drawing Tutorial  
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TgIYpe4dPWo 


Libraries (refer licenses.js) 

pixijs/pixijs - Graphics 
bjornharrtell/jsts – Polygon routines 
meodai/poline - Colour routines 
jwagner/simplex-noise - Noise gen 
strainer/fdrandom - Random number gen

metadata.name: CrossWorlds #284
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Dencity #562
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Deep Forest #299
metadata.description:
I love being in nature and impressionistic paintings. Deep Forest is my latest attempt to combine them with JavaScript. The editions will range from open, sparse forests to lush, dense, leafy wonderlands. Fall editions may render as Klimpt-style birch forests - my original inspiration for this work.

Best viewed on a computer. It may take a few seconds to start drawing and, depending on complexity, several minutes to finish rendering. In live view, press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 2318x3000px.

Features:
- One of the four seasons
- Rare 10% night version with 50/50 for normal fireflies or "fire" fireflies. Night will only be spring or summer.
- Amount of atmosphere/haze
- Horizon line near the middle or 30% "high horizon" near the top
- Tint from one of 8 light and 7 shadow colors
- Strength of the light and shadow color tint
- Mixed tree trunks or 30% all birch
- 50/50 moss on tree trunks
- One of 8 flower colors in spring or summer
- One of 4 perspective transforms
- Straight, curved out, or 30% curved inward trunks
- 50/50 grass in fall or winter
- 85% will have flowers in spring and summer
- 95% will have underbrush
- 50/50 clouds or solid background
- 50/50 solid background will be vertical or swirls
- Ground hill height

metadata.name: Drone Beast synthesizer #10
metadata.description:
This is a little Drone Beast with a modular synthesizer inside. Being made of thousands of particles swarming around several attractors it reacts on different signals across the modular patch. The patch itself is based on multiple 8-bit oscillators, modulating each other and being modulated by mathematical expressions, unique for each Beast.

Press anywhere in the frame to hear the sound. Use your mouse to explore the space of drone, which is individual for each Beast. Press "a" to toggle auto-evolution.

All remaining editions (if any) will be burnt in 2 days.

@ferluht, @alexexeev, 2022

metadata.name: Sketchbook Splash #305
metadata.description:
A splash of color on some scribbled shapes.

There are several keybindings to modify the image:
'1' - Toggles watercolors
'2' - Toggles overlaying constrast shapes 
'3' - Toggles sketch outlines
'4' - Toggles shape/splatter clipping (will fill the entire canvas with watercolor!)
'B' - Cycles borders; black, white, all colors in the palette being used, and no border

Play around to find something you like, and then press 'S' to download a copy of your image. 
You can also modify the URL parameters at the end of the URL to change the size of the image, such as &x=2560&y=1440. Keep in mind that this will result in a slightly different image, but colors/shapes/general layout will remain the same. The default size is 2048x2048.

@teaboswell, 2022

metadata.name: Ersbla #311
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Cosmic Type #2
metadata.description:
Cosmic Type is a kinetic type experiment that explores both graphic space as structural and semantic agency. Inspired by the early pioneering work of the concrete poets such as Dom Sylvester Houédard, Ian Hamilton Finley and Steve McCaffe, the project is a play with letters, words and graphic form in the computational and generative space.

Each iteration gives you the possibility to discover a variety of visual form through exploring the system. Please explore your iteration with the key interactions below. It is hoped that you give the time to explore and observe. If you don't, you may end up with just a blank canvas. 

Thank you for collecting. 

Key Interactions

‘a’ activates forward motion on/off
‘b’ activates backward motion on/off
‘r’ rotates grid 45° [ rotates on key pressed]
‘f’ rotates the grid freely [ stops on key release ]
‘p’ switches grid scale on/off [ this can be CPU heavy on older machines ] 
‘g’ extra glyphs on/off
‘q’ return to the initial state 


Program written by Mark Webster
Font is copyright ©simonrenaud

areafour.xyz
@motiondesign_01

metadata.name: Floatrest #226
metadata.description:
Floating forests over the endless sky, where birds, trees, plants, roots, rocks and waterfalls share an ecosystem full of life and emotion.

You can see some rain clouds in the sky and the sun shining under the raindrops.

The earth is moving, the blocks are falling, but the trees are strong in their roots.

Welcome to 'Floatrest'.

----

# Features

- 7 tree palettes
- 17 different background colors
- 10 different terrain colors
- clouds
- vines
- roots
- plants
- waterfall
- birds
- sun / moon
- night
- dark mode
- monochromatic
- 2 different aspect ratios (square & portrait)
- Press "p" on live mode to save in PNG

This artwork requires processing power and is intended for laptops and desktops primarily. It may take some time to render.

----

July 2022, gpitombo

metadata.name: Orchard #140
metadata.description:
A natural media rendering of a fruit tree during one of the four seasons. Sometimes, you'll catch it at night - with lights strung on the tree!

The amount of color in spring and fall, snow in winter, fruit on and off the tree will all vary. There are four spring bloom palettes, four trunk colors, and seven types of fruit. 

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1000x1000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

To render a variation at a new size, open live view and append '?size=#' to the end of the URL. The new size may be from 100 to 3,000. This version will not be a 1:1 match to your edition but will have all of the same features.

metadata.name: DisOrder #326
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 84 · 56 · 38 · 26 · 18  every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

All that is, starts with Order.

Order attempts to evade entropy by following its own intrinsic patterns. Then, inevitably, there is change: an anomaly, a nudge that turns into a catalyst for widespread change.The momentum cannot be stopped.

Brief cycles build upon themselves, iterating and breaking into something new with each turn. Now, looking back, the accumulation of small divergences look like a leap, with trails of evolutionary decline casting tall shadows on the patterns that bore them.

The beauty of what this entropy creates, rises beyond chaos. It represents the past, and signals the future, and suddenly looks like a wild take on Order itself – the true DisOrder of life.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

FEATURES :
21 Features implemented including colors, styles, technical parameters...

INTERACTIVITY :
Press ‘h’ in live mode for a list of options.
Press 's' to save an image of the output at the current resolution
Press ‘1’-’9’ to increase resolution
...

metadata.name: Dump of links #41
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork.
A blind spot in the metaverse full of junk broken links. Like dead neurons, they were left out of the system. Now they look for the closest thing to oxygen, and in a sonorous broken prelude, achieve synchro, so that one or at least two escape.

The work has 3 moments:
I. "Preludio en el fondo"
II. "Respiración de rotos"
III. "Grita y quema"

Original processed piano, flute and electronic samplers.
((click to start sound))

[s] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)

metadata.name: Kinetograms #296
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.
